# Prisma schema changes

Any change to `prisma/schema.prisma` (new model, new field, type change,
relation change, index change) must land as a single PR that contains **all
three** of:

1. **A migration**, generated via `npx prisma migrate dev --name <short_intent>`.
   Do **not** edit existing migrations under `prisma/migrations/`. If you need
   to revise a migration, create a new one. The migration file's first comment
   line must state the feature it enables (scoping §9.1).
   - `npx prisma db push` is for prototype iteration only. v0.2+ uses
     `prisma migrate dev` so the change is captured as an audited, replayable
     SQL artifact. Don't ship a schema change to a PR without a migration file.
2. **A seed update**, in `prisma/seed.ts`, so the deterministic dev dataset
   exercises the new shape. The seed clears all rows before insert; keep it
   idempotent.
3. **A PR** — never push schema changes directly to `main`. PR description
   must include: which feature this enables (link to F-number in scoping §2),
   the migration name, and a one-line note on backfill / data-migration
   strategy if existing rows are affected.

## Concretely

```bash
# good — migration + seed + PR
npx prisma migrate dev --name add_exception_request
# edit prisma/seed.ts to insert representative ExceptionRequest rows
git add prisma/schema.prisma prisma/migrations prisma/seed.ts
git commit -m "feat(db): add ExceptionRequest model (F8)"
gh pr create --fill
```

```bash
# bad — schema change without a migration / seed / PR
$ npx prisma db push                      # ❌ no migration artifact
$ git push origin main                    # ❌ no PR
```

## Authoritative-state schema rules

The dashboard owns authoritatively only `Decision`, `ExceptionRequest`, and
`ReclamationEvent` (scoping §3.3). For these three, every new field must be:

- **Append-only friendly.** No destructive defaults. Never drop a column once
  rows exist — add a new column and stop writing the old one.
- **Auditable.** Include a timestamp column where the row represents an event.
- **Reconstructable.** A field that can't be reconstructed from the policy
  repo + gateway log needs an explicit note in the migration comment
  explaining why the dashboard is the only source.

If the canonical schema in scoping §3.1 and `prisma/schema.prisma` disagree,
fix the schema and update the scoping doc in the same PR (or a follow-up doc
PR if the doc lives in another repo). See `data-model.mdc`.
